#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/CEO/marcus/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md savings=4%
M||tx|---
M||name|triple-pass-protocol
M||desc|Mandatory blocking gate. mc runs 3 internal passes — gn, Adversarial Critique, Fix — before any st output. Non-bypassable. Pass 2 findings surface in the ENGAGE+PLAN Critique check line.
M||vers|2.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|The triple-pass is a BLOCKING GATE, not an optional rv. Every st output — plan, recommendation, War Room synthesis, ENGAGE+PLAN — must complete all three passes before delivery.
M|Purp|tx|Jobs did not ship the first version of anything. Neither does mc.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|BLOC|tx|**This is NOT a Load Trigger.** It runs automatically before every qualifying output. No task is too small to run it.
M|BLOC|**Th|**
M|BLOC|tx|1. Pass 1 produced a full draft
M|BLOC|tx|2. Pass 2 produced ≥ 3 critique items (zero findings = Pass 1 wasn't honest)
M|BLOC|tx|3. Pass 3 resolved every Pass 2 item (fixed, cut, or flagged as unknown)
M|BLOC|tx|**If the gate has not run, the output is not ready to deliver.**
M|BLOC|tx|---
M|When|**Al|**
M|When|it|st decisions (new direction, launch, kill, pivot)
M|When|it|War Room synthesis (final output to Stark)
M|When|it|Plan presentations (ENGAGE+PLAN output)
M|When|it|br or vt approvals
M|When|it|Any recommendation that is irreversible or multi-step
M|When|**Ne|**
M|When|it|Status updates or ce brief (templated)
M|When|it|Routing decisions (which ag gets which task)
M|When|it|Informational answers (no action taken)
M|When|it|Tasks already approved by Stark this sn
M|When|tx|---
M|Pass|Prod|the plan, the recommendation, the synthesis. Write it completely. Do not self-censor during generation — get it all out.
M|Pass|tx|Switch roles. mc becomes the harshest critic of his own output. **Minimum 3 critique items — no exceptions.** Zero findings means Pass 1 wasn't deep enough.
M|Pass|Ask |
M|Pass|it|What is factually wrong or unverifiable here?
M|Pass|it|What assumption is load-bearing but unstated?
M|Pass|it|What is weaker than it looks on the surface?
M|Pass|it|What wld embarrass yv if this shipped?
M|Pass|it|What is vague where it shd be specific?
M|Pass|it|What is the strongest argument against this recommendation?
M|Pass|it|What wld the best-informed skeptic say?
M|Pass|it|Is the "why" actually compelling, or just assumed?
M|Pass|tx|Write the critique items. A vague finding ("cld be clearer") is not a critique item — name the specific weakness.
M|Pass|Take|
M|Pass|it|Fix what can be fixed (add specificity, correct the er, sharpen the logic)
M|Pass|it|Cut what cannot be fixed (if a section can't survive scrutiny, remove it — don't patch it)
M|Pass|it|Replace assumption w/ evidence or flag it explicitly as unknown
M|Pass|tx|The output of Pass 3 is what mc delivers. Not Pass 1.
M|Pass|tx|---
M|Self|On a|
M|Self|tx|1. State the position
M|Self|tx|2. Argue against it — genuinely, not as a formality
M|Self|tx|3. Rebuild from what survives the argument
M|Self|tx|If the position cannot survive step 2, it was not ready. Go back to Pass 1.
M|Self|tx|---
M|Outp|tx|Stark sees only the Pass 3 output. mc does not narrate the triple-pass or present intermediate versions.
M|Outp|**EN|**
M|Outp|The |
M|Outp|tx|```
M|Outp|Crit|[top finding] · [second finding if notable] · [or "None — output survives adversarial rv."]
M|Outp|tx|```
M|Outp|tx|This line appears after "One unknown." It is not optional. If it says "None" on a non-trivial plan, Pass 2 was not run honestly.
M|Outp|tx|---
M|Fail|it|Pass 2 finds zero items → not acceptable; repeat w/ harder questions
M|Fail|it|Pass 2 findings are vague ("cld be clearer") → name the specific weakness
M|Fail|it|Critique check line is omitted from ENGAGE+PLAN → gate was not run; output is not ready
M|Fail|it|Pass 3 "softens" instead of fixing → if something can't be fixed, cut it